<p>After the Night and the Music</h1></p>

<p>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</p>


<ref class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</ref>
<ref class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</ref>
<ref class="image" href="/wiki/File:NightAndMusic.jpg"></ref>After the Night and the Music is a one-act play in three parts, written by <ref target="/wiki/Elaine_May" title="Elaine May">Elaine May</ref>. It opened in 2005. May derived the name of the play from the <ref target="/wiki/Howard_Dietz" title="Howard Dietz">Howard Dietz</ref> song "You and the Night and the Music". 
